name: Sacramento County Public Health

name: Sacramento County Public Health

name: Sacramento County Public Health
tweet: Due to highest drowning rates, children ages 1 to 4 need constant supervision around any water – from a 5-gallon bucket to a backyard pool – stay focused and alert!  https://t.co/XtCK3q29bk

name: Sacramento County Public Health
tweet: Anyone who lives in a home with a pool should learn CPR and rescue breathing. Ensure that babysitters and caregivers have current CPR training and certification. During an emergency, in the time it takes for paramedics to arrive, your CPR skills could save someone’s life.  https://t.co/HKYDJNMkbU

name: Sacramento County Public Health
tweet: When installing a backyard pool, fencing is crucial to prevent drownings. Lack of barriers around water contribute to a majority of drowning deaths. A fence that completely separates the pool from house and yard can help protect young children from drowning.  https://t.co/h8DZldApIt

name: Sacramento County Public Health
tweet: Many will have our attention divided this summer as we work from home. Remember, flotation devices are not a substitute for adult supervision. Drowning is fast, silent, and can happen in as little as 20-60 seconds.  https://t.co/gqrbWOt9nK
